<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-644-405  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 644 405.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  May 25 1989 n1165 p11(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tigers stalk the financial jungle. (computer security in Londonfinancial institutions)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Collins, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An English consulting firm says it has been hired several times bycompanies to break into the companies' own computer systems as away to root out security flaws.andP;  The practice began in the UnitedStates, where the squads of hackers are called Tiger Teams afterUS Air Force counterintelligence teams.andP;  Corporate managers arewarned that failure of a Tiger Team to enter the system can leadto a false sense of security.andP;  UK critics of Tiger Teams saymorale can be damaged if employees discover the teams.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SecurityBankingAccess ControlsConsultantsAuditing of Computer SystemsIndustrial EspionageComputer HackersLaw EnforcementComputer Crimes.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>